{"_path":"/published-research/you-only-render-once","_dir":"published-research","_draft":false,"_partial":false,"_locale":"","title":"You Only Render Once","description":null,"icon":"lucide:bot","lastModified":"Jun 25, 2025","body":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tag":"h2","props":{"id":"you-only-render-once-enhancing-energy-and-computation-efficiency-of-mobile-virtual-reality"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"You Only Render Once: Enhancing Energy and Computation Efficiency of Mobile Virtual Reality"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Authors:"}]},{"type":"text","value":" "},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"https://xingyuchen.me/","rel":["nofollow"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Xingyu Chen"}]},{"type":"text","value":", "},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"https://fangxm.me/","rel":["nofollow"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Xinmin Fang"}]},{"type":"text","value":", Shuting Zhang, "},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"https://xyzhang.ucsd.edu/index.html","rel":["nofollow"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Xingyu Zhang"}]},{"type":"text","value":", Liang He, "},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"https://cse.ucdenver.edu/~lizheng/","rel":["nofollow"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Zhengxiong Li"}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h3","props":{"id":"abstract"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Abstract"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Mobile Virtual Reality (VR) is essential to achieving convenient and immersive human-computer interaction and realizing emerging applications such as Metaverse. However, existing VR technologies require two separate renderings of binocular images, causing a significant bottleneck for mobile devices with limited computing capability and power supply."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"This paper proposes an approach to rendering optimization for mobile VR called "},{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"You Only Render Once (YORO)"}]},{"type":"text","value":". By utilizing the per-pixel attribute, YORO can generate binocular VR images from the monocular image through genuinely one rendering, saving half the computation over conventional approaches."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Our evaluation indicates that, compared with the state-of-art, YORO can save "},{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"27% power consumption"}]},{"type":"text","value":" on average while achieving high binocular image quality ("},{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"0.9679 SSIM"}]},{"type":"text","value":" and "},{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"34.09 PSNR"}]},{"type":"text","value":") in mobile VR applications. Additionally, YORO can increase the frame rate by "},{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"115.2%"}]},{"type":"text","value":". These results corroborate YORO's superior computation/energy-saving performance, paving the road to a sustainable mobile VR."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h3","props":{"id":"demo-video"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Demo Video"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"video","props":{"width":"100%","height":400,"controls":true},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n  "},{"type":"element","tag":"source","props":{"src":"https://github.com/YORO-VR/YORO-VR.github.io/releases/download/Resource/demo.mp4","type":"video/mp4"},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\n  Your browser does not support the video tag.\n"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"em","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Demo Video for YORO in Scene Bistro, Sponza and Lost Empire. Running on Vivo IQOO 12."}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h3","props":{"id":"key-features"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Key Features"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"ul","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Universal Compatibility"}]},{"type":"text","value":": YORO is a general optimization technique compatible with "},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"https://www.khronos.org/openxr/","rel":["nofollow"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"OpenXR frameworks"}]},{"type":"text","value":", supporting various COTS VR devices such as Meta Quest, HTC Vive Focus, Pico Neo, Apple Vision Pro and more."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Production Ready"}]},{"type":"text","value":": YORO is production ready and can be directly applied to the Unity engine to support various VR games and applications."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Extensible Architecture"}]},{"type":"text","value":": YORO can serve as a cornerstone and be integrated with other optimization techniques such as Foveated Rendering and Asynchronous TimeWarp to further enhance the performance of VR applications."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Handles Close Objects"}]},{"type":"text","value":": YORO handles objects at very close distance without noticeable artifacts."}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h3","props":{"id":"performance-improvements"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Performance Improvements"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"ul","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"27% power consumption reduction"}]},{"type":"text","value":" on average"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"115.2% frame rate increase"}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"High binocular image quality: "},{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"0.9679 SSIM"}]},{"type":"text","value":" and "},{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"34.09 PSNR"}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"50% computation savings"}]},{"type":"text","value":" over conventional approaches"}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h3","props":{"id":"resources"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Resources"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"ul","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2506.15183","rel":["nofollow"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"ðŸ“„ Paper"}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"https://github.com/YORO-VR/YORO-VR","rel":["nofollow"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"ðŸ’» Code"}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"https://github.com/YORO-VR/YORO-VR/tree/main/data","rel":["nofollow"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"ðŸ“Š Data"}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"https://github.com/YORO-VR/YORO-VR.github.io/releases/download/Resource/YORO.unitypackage","rel":["nofollow"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"ðŸŽ® Unity Engine Plugin"}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"https://github.com/YORO